A message from Health Minister Dr Zweli Mkhize on South Africa’s latest efforts to flatten the curve and contain the spread of Covid-19. “Each one of us must make this a personal fight to save our nation. Stay calm, focused and courageous. Stay at home. Practice hygiene and distancing. Together, we will overcome. “ JOHANNESBURG - Health Minister Zweli Mkhize reminded the nation to comply with the national lockdown regulations. In a public service address, Mkhize explained what people can expect from the next phase of interventions. READ: COVID-19: SA death toll at 11 The minister said the internal transmission of the virus in the country is the next battle to be faced, and will be difficult to navigate as the accurate figures of infection might be masked by the lockdown. Mkhize described the forthcoming interventions, including mass testing to be rolled out to homes across the nation. READ: SA rolls out mobile testing in virus lockdown “Each one of us must make this a personal fight to save our nation," he said. "Stay calm, focused and courageous. Stay at home. Practice hygiene and distancing," he said. "Together, we will overcome. “ - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.